## 6. Core Functions

### `compute_all_scopes(df, scope_definitions) → DataFrame`

Main entry point. Loops through all scope definitions and adds boolean columns.

```python
df = compute_all_scopes(df, params["scopes"])
# Result: df with scope_us, scope_fortis, scope_bcef, scope_japan columns
```

### `compute_scope(df, scope_id, filters) → Series`

Computes a single scope. Builds AND condition from all filters.

### `get_scope_stats(df, scope_ids) → Dict`

Returns count statistics per scope.

```python
stats = get_scope_stats(df, ["us", "fortis", "bcef", "japan"])
# Result: {"total": 1000, "us": 150, "fortis": 200, "bcef": 80, "japan": 50, "multi_scope": 25}
```

