## 7. Usage Example

```python
import json
import pandas as pd
from lib.scope_utils import compute_all_scopes, get_scope_stats

# 1. Load config
with open("config/ccirc_params.json") as f:
    params = json.load(f)

# 2. Your input data
df = pd.DataFrame({
    "segment_id": ["S1", "S2", "S3"],
    "accounting_site_code_post_acc": ["12309", "10054", "30448"],
    "pmas_code_post_acc": ["PMA_01", "PMA_02", "PMA_05"],
    "lb_site_risque_apres_accr": ["Other", "Other", "Other"]
})

# 3. Compute scopes
df = compute_all_scopes(df, params["scopes"])

# 4. Result
print(df[["segment_id", "scope_us", "scope_fortis", "scope_japan"]])
#   segment_id  scope_us  scope_fortis  scope_japan
# 0         S1      True         False        False
# 1         S2     False          True        False
# 2         S3     False         False         True
```

